at second level.

32
00:02:42,295 --> 00:02:43,129
- Ah.

33
00:02:45,098 --> 00:02:47,167
- [Megan] I'll get it, Mom.

34
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,034
- Thanks honey.

35
00:02:48,034 --> 00:02:49,068
I can't move.

36
00:02:50,370 --> 00:02:51,638
- [Megan] Just relax, Mom.

37
00:02:51,638 --> 00:02:53,206
- I am relaxed.

38
00:02:53,206 --> 00:02:55,175
Haven't you seen a long
distance runner drop dead

39
00:02:55,175 --> 00:02:55,942
after a race?

40
00:02:55,942 --> 00:02:57,310
That's relaxed.

41
00:02:58,378 --> 00:03:00,713
- I guess that
means you're gonna

42
00:03:00,713 --> 00:03:02,048
want to take the elevator down?

43
00:03:04,384 --> 00:03:05,752
- Aren't you gonna
look at the view?

44
00:03:05,752 --> 00:03:06,953
- I'm trying.

45
00:03:06,953 --> 00:03:08,821
- Yeah but with that
thing stuck in your eye

46
00:03:08,821 --> 00:03:12,025
how can you enjoy the
sights, the atmosphere?

47
00:03:12,926 --> 00:03:13,927
- Sights.

48
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,062
The atmosphere.

49
00:03:16,062 --> 00:03:18,264
I'm soaking it all in, Mom.

50
00:03:20,266 --> 00:03:21,367
- Oh.

51
00:03:26,940 --> 00:03:29,943
You know when we were in
college, your father and I

52
00:03:29,943 --> 00:03:32,078
used to dream about coming here.

53
00:03:32,679 --> 00:03:35,982
Sitting where Fitzgerald
and Hemingway sat.

54
00:03:35,982 --> 00:03:38,585
- Well his priorities sure
have changed since then.

55
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:44,524
- I wonder if they paid
$5 for orange juice.

56
00:03:44,524 --> 00:03:45,925
- Could order wine.

57
00:03:45,925 --> 00:03:47,627
That's what the natives drink.

58
00:03:47,627 --> 00:03:48,628
It's cheaper.

59
00:03:50,129 --> 00:03:51,464
- Do you think there'll
be much drinking

60
00:03:51,464 --> 00:03:53,066
when you go away to college?

61
00:03:55,668 --> 00:03:57,604
- You mean am I
gonna get crazy drunk

62
00:03:57,604 --> 00:03:59,872
and wake up in some
strange motel room

