00:03:59,872 --> 00:04:02,642
and forget where I'm supposed
to take the com one final?

64
00:04:03,576 --> 00:04:04,344
- Hmm.

65
00:04:06,879 --> 00:04:08,581
- Maybe when I'm under stress.

66
00:04:09,349 --> 00:04:11,451
Come on or we'll miss the boat.

67
00:04:19,626 --> 00:04:21,394
- What a beautiful day!

68
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:23,963
I'm glad we're
going on the boat.

69
00:04:24,664 --> 00:04:26,366
I'm glad we're together.

70
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:31,170
(mysterious music)

71
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:34,540
- Constancia!

72
00:04:35,475 --> 00:04:36,809
Constancia.

73
00:04:39,245 --> 00:04:40,580
Constancia, it's me!

74
00:04:48,154 --> 00:04:49,322
- Joaquin.

75
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:51,057
- Incredible.

76
00:04:57,063 --> 00:04:58,264
Incredible.

77
00:04:59,899 --> 00:05:01,901
And more beautiful than ever.

78
00:05:03,002 --> 00:05:04,771
Some people thought
you were dead.

79
00:05:06,172 --> 00:05:09,108
Or perhaps had run off
to marry a rich gringo.

80
00:05:09,108 --> 00:05:10,109
(laughs)

81
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:13,780
How could you do that to
your friends, Constancia?

82
00:05:15,214 --> 00:05:16,249
- I tried.

83
00:05:17,083 --> 00:05:18,785
I wanted to explain.

84
00:05:18,785 --> 00:05:21,854
Oh, I've missed you,
how I've missed you.

85
00:05:23,923 --> 00:05:26,893
- So why did you run?

86
00:05:29,429 --> 00:05:30,997
- Can I trust you?

87
00:05:31,564 --> 00:05:34,100
There is so much to explain.

88
00:05:35,201 --> 00:05:37,270
Will you ever forgive me?

89
00:05:38,404 --> 00:05:40,573
I think we should
find a quiet place.

90
00:05:43,543 --> 00:05:46,245
(speaking foreign language)

91
00:05:46,245 --> 00:05:48,448
- [Tour Guide]
Ladies and gentlemen.

92
00:05:48,448 --> 00:05:50,616
The River Seine
winds through Paris

93
00:05:50,650 --> 00:05:55,355
approximately nine meters
below the level of the streets.

94
00:05:55,355 --> 00:05:59,625
On the left bank we see
(speaking foreign language).

95
00:06:01,094 --> 00:06:02,995
- [Joaquin] So Constancia.

96
00:06:02,995 --> 00:06:05,264
Paris seems to agree with you.

97
00:06:05,798 --> 00:06:08,634
- Oh I'm so glad to see
you, you have no idea.

98
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:10,303
I've missed you!

99
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:14,340
- I still can't believe
I found you again.

100
00:06:14,340 --> 00:06:15,475
- Oh yes.

101
00:06:15,475 --> 00:06:16,142
(laughing)

102
00:06:16,142 --> 00:06:17,510
- [Tour Guide] On
the left stands

103
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:19,946
the cathedral of Notre Dame.

104
00:06:19,946 --> 00:06:23,616
in 1163 Pope Alexander...
(inaudible dialogue)

105
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:27,487
The towers are 68 meters high.

106
00:06:27,487 --> 00:06:31,858
The north tower
contains 376 steps.

107
00:06:32,558 --> 00:06:36,229
(speaking foreign language)

108
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:45,104
(jackhammer rumbling)

109
00:06:51,377 --> 00:06:53,946
- Thought you wanted
a quiet place?

110
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:56,115
- A private place.

111
00:07:01,687 --> 00:07:04,657
(suspenseful music)

112
00:07:04,690 --> 00:07:08,561
- For a tete a tete or a deal?

113
00:07:12,231 --> 00:07:16,769
- [Tour Guide] For his
coronation in 1804.

114
00:07:17,537 --> 00:07:22,975
Only the three rose windows
retain their original glass.

115
00:07:30,082 --> 00:07:32,552
- A lot of money was
missing, Constancia.

116
00:07:34,687 --> 00:07:37,256
It's not just me
who has to forget.

117
00:07:39,058 --> 00:07:41,427
We answer to a big family.

118
00:07:42,061 --> 00:07:45,164
And we don't keep
things from family.

119
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:50,236
[Tour Guide]: 
(speaking foreign language)

120
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:03,516
- Wow.

121
00:08:03,516 --> 00:08:07,153
Mom, get a load of this.
- One second, hon.

122
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:08,387
- Just come here!

123
00:08:09,822 --> 00:08:10,957
Look, look!

124
00:08:16,963 --> 00:08:17,630
Do you see them?

125
00:08:17,663 --> 00:08:18,931
Authentic French lovers.

126
00:08:24,737 --> 00:08:25,805
(breathing heavily)

127
00:08:25,805 --> 00:08:27,840
- But you loved me once.

128
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:30,743
This is another chance for us.

129
00:08:31,978 --> 00:08:33,212
- I'm sorry.

130
00:08:40,653 --> 00:08:45,224
(gun fires)
(groans)

131
00:08:51,297 --> 00:08:53,065
- Do you see them?

132
00:08:57,270 --> 00:08:58,371
You missed it.

133
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:49,322
(splashes)

134
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:14,280
- [Tour Guide] The
new bridge is in fact

135
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:17,016
the oldest of the
sagittal bridges

136
00:10:17,016 --> 00:10:19,518
spanning the River Seine.

137
00:10:19,518 --> 00:10:20,853
Constructed in the late--

138
00:10:20,853 --> 00:10:22,321
- Hey down here!

139
00:10:26,525 --> 00:10:28,394
Hello!

140
00:10:28,427 --> 00:10:31,564
(exciting music)

141
00:10:43,409 --> 00:10:44,844
Hey Mom.
- Yeah?

142
00:10:44,844 --> 00:10:46,145
- Take a picture
of me for a change.

143
00:10:46,145 --> 00:10:47,079
- Okay, honey.

144
00:10:48,347 --> 00:10:49,615
Smile.

145
00:10:49,615 --> 00:10:51,250
You're so pretty.

146
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:52,418
Is it on?

147
00:10:52,418 --> 00:10:53,953
- No, you have to turn it on.

148
00:10:53,953 --> 00:10:55,454
- Where, here?

149
00:10:55,454 --> 00:10:56,522
- The red button.

150
00:10:57,156 --> 00:10:58,424
- The red button.

151
00:10:58,424 --> 00:11:00,793
- Mom, not
everything's difficult.

152
00:11:00,793 --> 00:11:02,428
- Wait til you have kids.

153
00:11:12,071 --> 00:11:14,807
(exciting music)

154
00:11:29,889 --> 00:11:32,258
Where are you
pointing that thing?

155
00:11:36,228 --> 00:11:37,897
- [Megan] Hunk city.

156
00:11:43,402 --> 00:11:45,738
- I know you're
past taking advice,

157
00:11:45,738 --> 00:11:48,574
but a little subtlety
never hurt a woman.

158
00:11:48,574 --> 00:11:49,341
- Right.

159
00:11:50,342 --> 00:11:51,310
Hey Tex.

160
00:11:55,915 --> 00:11:58,851
(exciting music)

161
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:15,568
(honking)

162
00:12:29,014 --> 00:12:30,149
- Come on.

163
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:00,246
- [Tour Guide] We hope
you have enjoyed your tour

164
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:01,547
on the Bateaux-Mouches.

165
00:13:01,580 --> 00:13:03,582
- Hey let me tell
you, youth hostels

166
00:13:03,582 --> 00:13:05,151
is the best way to see Europe.

167
00:13:05,151 --> 00:13:06,152
- Yeah?

168
00:13:06,152 --> 00:13:07,686
- New kids every day.

169
00:13:07,686 --> 00:13:09,789
Beaujolais Nouveau every night.

170
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:11,090
And party, party, party.

171
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:12,391
- Oh yeah.

172
00:13:12,391 --> 00:13:13,192
Yeah.

173
00:13:16,595 --> 00:13:17,663
- You know what?

174
00:13:17,696 --> 00:13:19,465
Some of us are gonna
go down to Lyon

175
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:20,599
on a bullet train.

176
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:22,301
And then we hit the
beaches at Cannes.

177
00:13:22,334 --> 00:13:24,003
Maybe a little sun and
some outrageous fun

178
00:13:24,003 --> 00:13:25,337
on the Cote d'Azure?

179
00:13:25,337 --> 00:13:26,505
Think you can stand it?

180
00:13:26,505 --> 00:13:28,374
- What, the Riviera?

181
00:13:28,374 --> 00:13:29,341
- You bet.

182
00:13:30,242 --> 00:13:31,577
Wanna come along?

183
00:13:33,145 --> 00:13:34,246
- Megan!

184
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:35,314
- Well?

185
00:13:36,949 --> 00:13:38,484
Stone fox.

186
00:13:39,552 --> 00:13:41,153
She with you?

187
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:42,288
(laughs)

188
00:13:42,288 --> 00:13:44,123
- That's my sister.

189
00:13:44,123 --> 00:13:46,091
We're just bumming
around together.

190
00:13:46,792 --> 00:13:48,460
She has this disease.

191
00:13:54,366 --> 00:13:55,701
- Allow me.

192
00:13:58,103 --> 00:13:59,271
Howdy, ma'am.

193
00:14:00,105 --> 00:14:01,040
- Thank you.

194
00:14:04,643 --> 00:14:07,546
(suspenseful music)

195
00:14:31,937 --> 00:14:34,206
Barbara Brennan.

196
00:14:36,642 --> 00:14:38,277
Barbara Brennan.

197
00:14:44,083 --> 00:14:45,951
(screams)

198
00:14:45,985 --> 00:14:47,419
- Mom.
(screaming)

199
00:14:47,453 --> 00:14:49,521
Mom please just watch the road!

200
00:14:49,521 --> 00:14:51,590
- Oh, oh!
- This is insane!

201
00:14:53,592 --> 00:14:54,426
Just go for it.

202
00:14:54,426 --> 00:14:55,661
- Go for it?

203
00:14:55,661 --> 00:14:56,595
We're trapped!

204
00:14:56,595 --> 00:14:57,897
Oh my god!

205
00:14:57,930 --> 00:14:59,131
Is there a car over there?

206
00:14:59,131 --> 00:15:01,033
- Mom, there are 100 of them.

207
00:15:01,033 --> 00:15:02,134
- Why don't we forget
the car's registered

208
00:15:02,134 --> 00:15:03,569
in my name and you drive?

209
00:15:03,569 --> 00:15:05,638
- No mom this is great,
every man for himself.

210
00:15:05,638 --> 00:15:06,605
Just go for it.

211
00:15:06,605 --> 00:15:08,674
- Oh my god, shoo, move!

212
00:15:08,674 --> 00:15:09,942
- [Megan] Mom.

213
00:15:09,942 --> 00:15:11,176
Mom.

214
00:15:11,176 --> 00:15:12,578
- Don't talk to me, I'm
trying to concentrate.

215
00:15:12,578 --> 00:15:13,712
- Alright look out!
(honks)

216
00:15:14,546 --> 00:15:15,114
Look out!

217
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:16,482
- Why are you yelling?

218
00:15:16,482 --> 00:15:18,150
- Because Mom, this is
insane, this is insane.

219
00:15:18,150 --> 00:15:19,385
- Will you stop yelling!

220
00:15:19,718 --> 00:15:21,520
- [Megan] I don't
wanna die, okay?

221
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:22,821
- Calm down or I'll kill you!

222
00:15:22,821 --> 00:15:24,890
- God, no wonder Dad
couldn't live with you.

223
00:15:24,890 --> 00:15:26,025
- What?

224
00:15:26,025 --> 00:15:27,593
What did you say?

225
00:15:28,494 --> 00:15:31,130
- Mom just watch the road.

226
00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:32,898
- That was a horrible
thing to say!

227
00:15:32,898 --> 00:15:34,033
- Just watch the road!

228
00:15:34,066 --> 00:15:35,334
- Why are you so hostile?

229
00:15:35,334 --> 00:15:36,001
- Hostile?

230
00:15:36,035 --> 00:15:38,070
I'm not hostile, I'm bored.

231
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:39,972
Oh my god we've
gone around again.

232
00:15:39,972 --> 00:15:41,206
What, bored?

233
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,341
- [Megan] Mom let
me out of here.

234
00:15:42,374 --> 00:15:43,842
- I had to work my
fingers to the bone

235
00:15:43,876 --> 00:15:45,911
to pay for this trip
and you call it boring?

236
00:15:45,911 --> 00:15:48,213
- Mom, I didn't want
this, this was your idea!

237
00:15:48,213 --> 00:15:49,949
- You're going away to
school for two years,

238
00:15:49,949 --> 00:15:51,583
I thought it would be fun!

239
00:15:51,583 --> 00:15:52,418
- Fun?

240
00:15:52,418 --> 00:15:53,519
This is crazy!

241
00:15:53,519 --> 00:15:54,853
- Oh, now I'm crazy.

242
00:15:54,853 --> 00:15:57,423
- Mom, look, I'm
transferring schools, okay?

243
00:15:57,423 --> 00:15:59,425
I'm not entering
the foreign legion.

244
00:15:59,425 --> 00:16:00,359
You're acting like
we're never going

245
00:16:00,359 --> 00:16:01,260
to see each other again.

246
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:02,194
That's crazy.

247
00:16:02,194 --> 00:16:03,595
- No.

248
00:16:03,595 --> 00:16:05,297
Not crazy.

249
00:16:05,297 --> 00:16:06,832
Wishful thinking.

250
00:16:06,832 --> 00:16:09,735
- Fine, fine, I'm outta here.

251
00:16:09,735 --> 00:16:11,870
Abandon me then, abandon me.

252
00:16:14,039 --> 00:16:15,174
- Wait a minute!

253
00:16:15,174 --> 00:16:16,008
Where are you going?

254
00:16:16,008 --> 00:16:16,909
Get back in here.

255
00:16:16,909 --> 00:16:18,210
- No.

256
00:16:18,210 --> 00:16:21,680
- I've never abandoned
anyone in my whole life.

257
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:23,682
- What do you call this then?

258
00:16:23,682 --> 00:16:25,017
- Megan.

259
00:16:27,286 --> 00:16:28,320
(sighs)

260
00:16:37,262 --> 00:16:43,936
(light music)

261
00:16:53,245 --> 00:16:55,681
- You seemed a
little distracted.

262
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:57,349
I must be getting old.

263
00:16:58,150 --> 00:16:58,650
- You?

264
00:16:58,684 --> 00:16:59,385
(glasses clink)

265
00:16:59,418 --> 00:17:00,652
Never.

266
00:17:01,253 --> 00:17:02,921
I'm just...

267
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:06,792
- What is it, my little one?

268
00:17:07,159 --> 00:17:08,360
Hmm?

269
00:17:09,294 --> 00:17:10,763
Tell me what it is.

270
00:17:10,763 --> 00:17:13,499
- Oh it's just...

271
00:17:14,433 --> 00:17:17,202
It's just some awful
American women.

272
00:17:18,670 --> 00:17:21,206
They crash into me in their car.

273
00:17:24,843 --> 00:17:27,846
I have one of their
names written someplace.

274
00:17:33,919 --> 00:17:36,789
They said they had insurance

275
00:17:36,789 --> 00:17:41,660
but I was so furious I didn't
get where they were staying.

276
00:17:44,863 --> 00:17:47,032
- I suppose I could
locate their hotel

277
00:17:47,866 --> 00:17:49,601
if they are in Paris.

278
00:17:49,601 --> 00:17:53,072
- No Bernard, that's
asking too much.

279
00:17:53,705 --> 00:17:55,140
- You didn't ask.

280
00:17:56,308 --> 00:17:57,443
- No not really.

281
00:17:58,610 --> 00:18:00,879
It's just a private matter.

282
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:04,349
- And I'll do it.

283
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:06,118
Because I adore you.

284
00:18:07,786 --> 00:18:08,987
Now come to me.

285
00:18:26,338 --> 00:18:27,172
- Hi.

286
00:18:31,677 --> 00:18:33,278
We still talking?

287
00:18:34,246 --> 00:18:35,581
- Hmm.

288
00:18:35,581 --> 00:18:38,317
I've had some time
to do some thinking

289
00:18:38,317 --> 00:18:41,820
and I'm going to accept you
now as a responsible woman

290
00:18:41,820 --> 00:18:47,025
and I agree that you have
every right to live your life

291
00:18:47,059 --> 00:18:48,560
any way you choose to.

292
00:18:50,529 --> 00:18:51,363
- Okay.

293
00:18:52,331 --> 00:18:55,601
Listen I apologize for
what I said before.

294
00:18:57,903 --> 00:18:59,638
- No need to apologize.

295
00:19:00,272 --> 00:19:01,907
I've forgotten all about it.

296
00:19:01,907 --> 00:19:02,741
- Good.

297
00:19:04,843 --> 00:19:06,678
- Organizers claimed
the demonstration

298
00:19:06,678 --> 00:19:08,981
as overwhelming success.

299
00:19:08,981 --> 00:19:10,048
- You gonna change?

300
00:19:10,048 --> 00:19:11,850
- To the equality of all people.

301
00:19:11,850 --> 00:19:12,818
- For what?

302
00:19:13,719 --> 00:19:15,087
- Well I thought we'd--

303
00:19:15,087 --> 00:19:16,555
- Elsewhere today,
a gruesome discovery

304
00:19:16,555 --> 00:19:18,857
in the shadow of Notre Dame.

305
00:19:18,857 --> 00:19:20,859
A man was shot to death.

306
00:19:20,859 --> 00:19:24,329
Police identified the
victim as Joaquin Prades.

307
00:19:24,329 --> 00:19:27,099
Prades was the son of
a Panamanian diplomat

308
00:19:27,099 --> 00:19:29,568
who was forced into
retirement last year

309
00:19:29,568 --> 00:19:32,070
because of the family's
reputed connections

310
00:19:32,070 --> 00:19:33,639
to the South American mafia.

311
00:19:33,639 --> 00:19:35,207
- I want this to
be our vacation.

312
00:19:35,207 --> 00:19:37,342
- Police will not speculate--
- Me too.

313
00:19:37,342 --> 00:19:39,144
We'll do whatever you wanna do.

314
00:19:39,144 --> 00:19:41,213
- [Reporter] Prades's father,
interviewed by telephone--

315
00:19:41,246 --> 00:19:42,080
- Okay.

316
00:19:42,114 --> 00:19:43,849
- [Reporter] Said he
was shocked and grieved.

317
00:19:43,882 --> 00:19:45,817
He said that he hoped
his son's killers

318
00:19:45,817 --> 00:19:47,452
would be brought to justice.

319
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:50,088
- Wait, Mom, the Moulin Rouge.

320
00:19:50,088 --> 00:19:51,490
Isn't that a tourist trap?

321
00:19:51,490 --> 00:19:53,992
I mean like a floor
show like Las Vegas.

322
00:19:53,992 --> 00:19:56,261
- No, like Shirley
MacLaine in Can Can

323
00:19:56,261 --> 00:19:59,331
or Jose Ferrer when he
played Toulouse Lautrec.

324
00:19:59,331 --> 00:20:01,400
Besides, we don't have to drive.

325
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,601
- That's a blessing.

326
00:20:02,601 --> 00:20:04,803
Hey, two American
girls out on the town.

327
00:20:04,803 --> 00:20:06,471
Parisian men watch out.

328
00:20:06,471 --> 00:20:07,940
(laughs)

329
00:20:11,643 --> 00:20:14,746
(suspenseful music)

330
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:29,094
- [Barbara] The desk clerk said

331
00:20:29,094 --> 00:20:31,930
it's two blocks down
and to the left.

332
00:20:32,364 --> 00:20:33,932
Or is it to the right?

333
00:20:35,801 --> 00:20:39,271
- Here we got French
fries being whipped up by,

334
00:20:40,172 --> 00:20:43,909
I dunno, he's an
off-duty gourmet chef.

335
00:20:47,746 --> 00:20:51,750
(speaking foreign language)

336
00:20:53,118 --> 00:20:55,420
- Food food...

337
00:20:55,454 --> 00:20:56,388
Oh, here we go.

338
00:20:56,388 --> 00:21:00,392
On duty we have French business
women finalizing a deal.

339
00:21:00,392 --> 00:21:02,561
- And somewhere there's
a Parisian mother

340
00:21:02,561 --> 00:21:05,731
who wishes she'd kept a
closer look on her daughter.

341
00:21:05,731 --> 00:21:06,665
- Mom!

342
00:21:07,766 --> 00:21:08,967
- Put it down.

343
00:21:11,670 --> 00:21:14,306
(speaking foreign language)

344
00:21:16,808 --> 00:21:19,811
(suspenseful music)

345
00:21:24,516 --> 00:21:27,286
I don't know if walking in
this part of town, oh my god,

346
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:28,887
is such a good idea.

347
00:21:29,254 --> 00:21:32,491
- It's a terrible idea,
madame, mademoiselle.

348
00:21:32,491 --> 00:21:34,159
Very much fun here.

349
00:21:34,159 --> 00:21:35,427
Very nice here.

350
00:21:35,427 --> 00:21:37,996
Very nice, beautiful
ladies, nice ladies.

351
00:21:37,996 --> 00:21:40,299
- No we--
- Very special, very artistic.

352
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:42,334
No cover charge, no no no no no.

353
00:21:42,334 --> 00:21:43,402
Okay?

354
00:21:43,402 --> 00:21:44,636
- No, okay.

355
00:21:44,636 --> 00:21:45,837
- You're American, I bet you!

356
00:21:45,837 --> 00:21:48,640
- We are and we're--
- Yes, come in, come in!

357
00:21:49,241 --> 00:21:50,442
- Hey!

358
00:21:50,442 --> 00:21:51,310
(screaming)

359
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:53,512
(shouting)

360
00:21:57,349 --> 00:21:59,818
Call the police, the police!

361
00:22:00,352 --> 00:22:01,486
Oh my god.

362
00:22:04,456 --> 00:22:06,325
(honking)

363
00:22:06,358 --> 00:22:08,160
Call the police, something!

364
00:22:08,193 --> 00:22:10,796
(screaming)

365
00:22:11,963 --> 00:22:14,132
Police, somebody help us!

366
00:22:14,166 --> 00:22:15,334
- What's the problem?

367
00:22:15,334 --> 00:22:16,935
- Sir, please, call the police!

368
00:22:16,935 --> 00:22:18,103
- Alright madam.

369
00:22:18,870 --> 00:22:19,805
What's the problem?

370
00:22:19,838 --> 00:22:21,173
- He is the police.

371
00:22:22,207 --> 00:22:24,476
- Somebody took my purse,
a man took my purse.

372
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:25,577
- What man?

373
00:22:27,846 --> 00:22:29,781
Can you describe him?

374
00:22:29,781 --> 00:22:30,916
- Yes.

375
00:22:30,916 --> 00:22:33,852
He was, uh, well...

376
00:22:34,986 --> 00:22:38,890
He was wearing a gold
earring, I think.

377
00:22:38,890 --> 00:22:41,093
- How much money did
you have in your purse?

378
00:22:41,960 --> 00:22:44,229
- He didn't actually
take any money.

379
00:22:44,696 --> 00:22:46,465
- What did your purse look like?

380
00:22:49,468 --> 00:22:51,002
I see.

381
00:22:51,002 --> 00:22:52,437
That's the purse he took?

382
00:22:53,905 --> 00:22:54,706
- Yes.

383
00:22:55,907 --> 00:22:56,708
- Yes.

384
00:23:00,779 --> 00:23:02,481
(murmuring)

385
00:23:02,514 --> 00:23:08,220
An unknown assailant
attempted to steal my purse

386
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:12,257
but was unsuccessful.

387
00:23:13,024 --> 00:23:14,259
Is that it?

388
00:23:15,794 --> 00:23:17,796
- It was an attempted robbery.

389
00:23:18,363 --> 00:23:20,132
- I am attempting to help.

390
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:23,135
- Then why aren't
you chasing him?

391
00:23:23,668 --> 00:23:25,337
- An unknown assailant--

392
00:23:25,337 --> 00:23:28,940
- Thank you very
much for your help.

393
00:23:36,248 --> 00:23:37,482
- Madame Brennan?

394
00:23:39,818 --> 00:23:41,720
Here is the telephone
number of my precinct

395
00:23:41,753 --> 00:23:43,488
with my extension.

396
00:23:43,488 --> 00:23:45,524
If something more
concrete comes to mind,

397
00:23:45,524 --> 00:23:47,726
please feel free to call me.

398
00:23:48,627 --> 00:23:49,461
Voila.

399
00:23:53,331 --> 00:23:55,867
- Voila to you too, buddy!

400
00:23:55,901 --> 00:23:57,135
- Mom.

401
00:24:00,472 --> 00:24:02,441
He was cute, wasn't he?

402
00:24:03,475 --> 00:24:05,143
- That's enough for one night.

403
00:24:10,982 --> 00:24:12,217
(dramatic music)

404
00:24:12,217 --> 00:24:15,120
- Oh my god.
- Oh my.

405
00:24:25,263 --> 00:24:29,534
(murmuring)
(phones ringing)

406
00:24:29,568 --> 00:24:33,338
- Why do you suppose
the chief works so late?

407
00:24:34,906 --> 00:24:37,943
Doesn't have to deal with
pickpockets and pimps anymore.

408
00:24:39,544 --> 00:24:40,812
Why?

409
00:24:40,812 --> 00:24:42,013
Hemery!

410
00:24:42,447 --> 00:24:45,116
- Well I never thought about it.

411
00:24:45,717 --> 00:24:47,686
- I'll tell you why.

412
00:24:47,719 --> 00:24:48,920
Dedication?

413
00:24:49,454 --> 00:24:50,689
No.

414
00:24:50,689 --> 00:24:52,724
This is dedication.

415
00:24:53,992 --> 00:24:55,393
Ambition.

416
00:24:56,561 --> 00:24:57,729
And you know what?

417
00:24:57,762 --> 00:24:59,464
I don't like him.

418
00:25:00,131 --> 00:25:01,700
Have you ever seen
his lady friend?

419
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:02,934
- Nn nnn.

420
00:25:03,835 --> 00:25:07,606
- What about the townhouse,
the country place, or the cars?

421
00:25:07,606 --> 00:25:09,040
On his salary?

422
00:25:09,241 --> 00:25:10,308
No.

423
00:25:10,308 --> 00:25:11,543
His wife's money.

424
00:25:12,277 --> 00:25:14,312
And I'll tell you what.

425
00:25:14,312 --> 00:25:16,281
It's not fair.

426
00:25:16,281 --> 00:25:18,583
It's not fair for one
man to have so much.

427
00:25:20,685 --> 00:25:22,087
- Alibert.

428
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:23,154
- Me?

429
00:25:24,623 --> 00:25:25,891
- Now.

430
00:25:31,963 --> 00:25:34,633
(phone ringing)

431
00:25:37,502 --> 00:25:38,637
- Oui?

432
00:25:39,704 --> 00:25:40,772
Ah.

433
00:25:41,740 --> 00:25:43,308
Madame Brennan.

434
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:45,944
(knocking)

435
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:50,215
Here I am.

436
00:25:57,322 --> 00:25:59,791
- Is this concrete
enough for you?

437
00:26:10,702 --> 00:26:12,304
- What is missing?

438
00:26:13,538 --> 00:26:16,808
- A light summer jacket.

439
00:26:19,244 --> 00:26:23,248
- We didn't see anyone and
neither did anyone else.

440
00:26:23,248 --> 00:26:26,518
I checked with the desk clerk
and he spoke with the maid.

441
00:26:27,352 --> 00:26:28,653
- Very good.

442
00:26:29,821 --> 00:26:31,957
I take it you don't have jewels.

443
00:26:33,058 --> 00:26:35,894
- Well I didn't bring any
with me when I came to Paris

444
00:26:35,894 --> 00:26:37,395
if that's what you mean.

445
00:26:40,098 --> 00:26:42,601
- I assume you're carrying
your money with you.

446
00:26:42,601 --> 00:26:43,802
- Yes.

447
00:26:43,802 --> 00:26:45,670
- That's why nothing was taken.

448
00:26:48,406 --> 00:26:50,976
My best guess is that
you have been the victim

449
00:26:50,976 --> 00:26:53,311
of two unfortunate
circumstances.

450
00:26:53,311 --> 00:26:55,580
I'm sure these things
happen in America.

451
00:26:56,247 --> 00:26:57,182
- Yes.

452
00:26:57,983 --> 00:27:01,252
But not all the time
and everywhere we go.

453
00:27:01,853 --> 00:27:04,189
This is not a coincidence!

454
00:27:04,189 --> 00:27:06,257
And in America when a
citizen is in trouble,

455
00:27:06,257 --> 00:27:08,259
the police actually try to help!

456
00:27:08,259 --> 00:27:10,528
And even when the citizen
doesn't happen to be American

457
00:27:10,528 --> 00:27:12,464
the police still try to help!

458
00:27:13,832 --> 00:27:15,300
- Yeah.

459
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:16,067
(clock ticking)
(suspenseful music)

460
00:27:16,067 --> 00:27:17,969
- [Daniel] You want
an investigation?

461
00:27:17,969 --> 00:27:18,970
You've got it.

462
00:27:30,882 --> 00:27:32,450
- Shall I dust the panties?

463
00:27:32,817 --> 00:27:34,019
(shutter clicks)

464
00:27:34,052 --> 00:27:35,453
I'm running out of film.

465
00:27:39,958 --> 00:27:41,326
- Take your time.

466
00:27:47,832 --> 00:27:51,236
Good job boys, I'll see
you're recommended for medals.

467
00:27:51,403 --> 00:27:53,171
- [Alibert] A request will do.

468
00:28:03,748 --> 00:28:06,017
- The room has been
thoroughly checked.

469
00:28:06,017 --> 00:28:09,621
Your presence will no longer
contaminate the crime scene.

470
00:28:09,621 --> 00:28:13,091
Therefore you may
return momentarily.

471
00:28:15,894 --> 00:28:16,995
- Um--

472
00:28:16,995 --> 00:28:18,196
- I need to
fingerprint you first.

473
00:28:18,196 --> 00:28:19,130
- You what?

474
00:28:19,130 --> 00:28:20,165
- Fingerprints.

475
00:28:23,068 --> 00:28:25,937
I need to compare what I've
taken from the room to...

476
00:28:28,707 --> 00:28:30,442
I need to fingerprint you.

477
00:28:36,081 --> 00:28:39,584
- Alright, we're
humiliated, we're tired.

478
00:28:39,584 --> 00:28:41,286
You've had a real good
time pushing us around

479
00:28:41,286 --> 00:28:42,787
and you've kept us
up half the night.

480
00:28:42,787 --> 00:28:43,822
Congratulations.

481
00:28:43,822 --> 00:28:44,789
- Touche.

482
00:28:45,657 --> 00:28:46,558
(suspenseful music)
(gasps)

483
00:28:46,558 --> 00:28:47,425
- There he is!

484
00:28:47,425 --> 00:28:48,927
- Who?
- The man!

485
00:28:48,927 --> 00:28:52,263
The man who took our purse!
- Oh my god!

486
00:28:52,263 --> 00:28:54,866
- Hey!
- Hey stop, stop!

487
00:28:54,866 --> 00:28:57,368
(speaking foreign language)

488
00:28:57,368 --> 00:28:58,903
- Stop him!
- Get him, get him!

489
00:28:58,903 --> 00:29:01,139
(shouting)

490
00:29:05,110 --> 00:29:06,544
(tires squealing)

491
00:29:06,544 --> 00:29:08,880
- Stop, police, stop!

492
00:29:12,917 --> 00:29:14,085
- [Daniel] Did you
get the license?

493
00:29:14,119 --> 00:29:15,653
- No sir, the lights were off.

494
00:29:15,653 --> 00:29:16,788
- Get on the radio.

495
00:29:18,156 --> 00:29:21,593
(mysterious music)

496
00:29:26,431 --> 00:29:28,633
I caused you a
great inconvenience.

497
00:29:29,234 --> 00:29:31,636
I didn't take you
seriously enough.

498
00:29:34,739 --> 00:29:36,207
Forgive me, madame.

499
00:29:37,709 --> 00:29:39,043
- Apology accepted.

500
00:29:40,378 --> 00:29:43,281
- Until I know what to
make of these events,

501
00:29:43,281 --> 00:29:45,750
caution on your part is
certainly called for.

502
00:29:47,218 --> 00:29:48,186
- Caution.

503
00:29:50,822 --> 00:29:54,058
Is going back to Philadelphia
cautious enough for you?

504
00:29:54,492 --> 00:29:56,661
- With your permission, madame,

505
00:29:56,661 --> 00:29:59,597
we'd like to move you
to a different hotel.

506
00:29:59,597 --> 00:30:02,066
A place where no one
knows where you are.

507
00:30:05,303 --> 00:30:06,938
(speaking foreign language)

508
00:30:11,109 --> 00:30:13,511
- Does this seem normal to you?

509
00:30:15,647 --> 00:30:16,681
- Mom.

510
00:30:16,714 --> 00:30:19,250
Why can't you just
relax and enjoy it?

511
00:30:20,385 --> 00:30:24,289
Maybe the inspector knows the
manager's cousin or something

512
00:30:24,289 --> 00:30:27,659
and he wanted you to
stay in a nice place.

513
00:30:29,127 --> 00:30:31,229
'Cause he probably
has a crush on you.

514
00:30:32,797 --> 00:30:37,101
- For a guy who started
out to be such a pill

515
00:30:38,403 --> 00:30:40,572
he sure came a long way.

516
00:30:40,572 --> 00:30:43,741
- You came on pretty strong,
I was kinda proud of you.

517
00:30:45,443 --> 00:30:46,544
- Yeah?

518
00:30:48,613 --> 00:30:51,749
Well, he did push all
the wrong buttons.

519
00:30:52,717 --> 00:30:54,819
Of course he did apologize but

520
00:30:55,153 --> 00:30:57,488
maybe we should have gone home.

521
00:30:59,591 --> 00:31:00,391
(sighs)

522
00:31:00,425 --> 00:31:03,161
- What, because of
a couple of mishaps?

523
00:31:05,597 --> 00:31:08,132
- At least no one
knows where we are.

524
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:10,935
- That's right.

525
00:31:14,706 --> 00:31:16,140
Goodnight, Mom.

526
00:31:17,108 --> 00:31:18,209
- Night, honey.

527
00:31:20,578 --> 00:31:22,313
- Day two.

528
00:31:22,313 --> 00:31:23,915
Very nice.

529
00:31:23,915 --> 00:31:25,516
The way things should be.

530
00:31:26,784 --> 00:31:29,721
Very ritzy, very,
oh, there's Mother

531
00:31:29,721 --> 00:31:33,124
looking very
stylishly undercover.

532
00:31:33,124 --> 00:31:35,093
She's a little jumpy in
this high-rent district.

533
00:31:35,093 --> 00:31:37,428
Thinks there must be a catch.

534
00:31:45,303 --> 00:31:47,538
- Hi honey.
- Hi Mom.

535
00:31:48,006 --> 00:31:50,008
Hey, things are looking up, huh?

536
00:31:52,510 --> 00:31:54,245
- We should stay together.

537
00:31:54,245 --> 00:31:55,613
Or the more I think of it.

538
00:31:56,748 --> 00:31:58,216
We should leave Paris.

539
00:32:01,219 --> 00:32:04,188
(suspenseful music)

540
00:32:10,328 --> 00:32:11,429
What's wrong?

541
00:32:13,665 --> 00:32:15,166
