00:48:21,765 --> 00:48:22,833
- Oh look.

811
00:48:22,833 --> 00:48:25,636
Okay wait, here Mom,
hold my bag, hold my bag.

812
00:48:25,669 --> 00:48:26,803
- Okay.

813
00:48:28,372 --> 00:48:29,940
He is a cutie.

814
00:48:33,377 --> 00:48:35,112
(singing in foreign language)

815
00:48:53,063 --> 00:48:55,232
- God, did you see those hats?

816
00:49:04,074 --> 00:49:05,809
- Those look great on you.

817
00:49:11,882 --> 00:49:14,017
- Ooh, that one's great.

818
00:49:19,356 --> 00:49:20,390
What do you think?

819
00:49:20,424 --> 00:49:21,224
(laughs)

820
00:49:21,258 --> 00:49:22,492
- [Luc] Fantastic.

821
00:49:22,926 --> 00:49:24,194
- Mom'll die.

822
00:49:25,262 --> 00:49:28,131
- Escargot, that's the
only French I know.

823
00:49:28,165 --> 00:49:29,700
(laughing)

824
00:49:31,668 --> 00:49:33,236
- I'm glad we came here.

825
00:49:38,475 --> 00:49:40,844
I don't get to flea
markets much back home.

826
00:49:40,844 --> 00:49:43,080
Probably because there aren't
any flea markets back home.

827
00:49:43,080 --> 00:49:44,348
(suspenseful music)

828
00:49:44,348 --> 00:49:46,149
I hear they've got some
great ones in New York,

829
00:49:46,149 --> 00:49:47,617
I mean among other things.

830
00:49:50,787 --> 00:49:52,222
- [Luc] You're talking too much.

831
00:49:52,222 --> 00:49:53,824
- [Megan] New York's probably
where I'm gonna end up.

832
00:49:53,824 --> 00:49:56,693
There's no way I'm gonna
stay around where I live now.

833
00:50:06,103 --> 00:50:07,504
- We'd better find them.

834
00:50:07,504 --> 00:50:09,606
- Okay, I'll check
back this way.

835
00:50:09,606 --> 00:50:11,141
- Alright, I'll
meet you back here.

836
00:50:11,141 --> 00:50:11,975
- Okay.

837
00:50:19,616 --> 00:50:21,518
- [Megan] Nearly
there, just a sec.

838
00:50:22,652 --> 00:50:24,121
- [Luc] Let me see you.

839
00:50:26,656 --> 00:50:27,657
- [Megan] Like it?

840
00:50:29,159 --> 00:50:35,132
- Lovely but you
should keep quiet.

841
00:50:49,312 --> 00:50:50,247
- Megan?

842
00:50:52,049 --> 00:50:54,151
- No, no, no, no!

843
00:50:56,086 --> 00:50:58,021
- Oh my, oh my!

844
00:50:58,688 --> 00:50:59,890
- No, no!

845
00:50:59,890 --> 00:51:01,858
No!

846
00:51:02,659 --> 00:51:04,394
- Megan!

847
00:51:04,428 --> 00:51:05,929
Help!

848
00:51:05,929 --> 00:51:07,064
Daniel!

849
00:51:08,598 --> 00:51:10,067
Megan!

850
00:51:10,100 --> 00:51:13,103
(dramatic music)

851
00:51:14,571 --> 00:51:17,174
- No, no, please god!

852
00:51:19,409 --> 00:51:21,978
(shouting)

853
00:51:21,978 --> 00:51:23,280
Oh god!

854
00:51:31,154 --> 00:51:32,222
No!

855
00:51:36,493 --> 00:51:38,128
- Oh, oh!

856
00:51:41,364 --> 00:51:43,133
Megan!
- Hey!

857
00:51:43,500 --> 00:51:44,668
Hey you, stop!

858
00:51:45,802 --> 00:51:47,237
You, stop, police!

859
00:51:47,237 --> 00:51:48,038
Get off!

860
00:51:48,772 --> 00:51:50,507
- Hey, hey!

861
00:51:58,582 --> 00:52:01,585
- Madame Brennan,
please follow me.

862
00:52:01,585 --> 00:52:03,420
- What have you
done to my daughter?

863
00:52:03,420 --> 00:52:04,421
- Walk.

864
00:52:04,454 --> 00:52:06,223
You'll find out soon enough.

865
00:52:07,390 --> 00:52:09,960
(groaning)

866
00:52:23,140 --> 00:52:25,542
(honking)

867
00:52:33,984 --> 00:52:36,586
(gun fires)

868
00:52:51,168 --> 00:52:52,002
- Hey!

869
00:52:52,369 --> 00:52:54,237
(speaking foreign language)

870
00:52:54,237 --> 00:52:55,405
Give it back!

871
00:52:56,106 --> 00:52:57,541
- Where did the lady go?

872
00:52:57,541 --> 00:52:58,708
- That lady?
- Yeah.

873
00:52:58,742 --> 00:53:02,045
- A guy with a gun, a
silencer, grabs her.

874
00:53:02,078 --> 00:53:03,580
- What guy?
- What's going on?

875
00:53:03,580 --> 00:53:04,447
- What guy?

876
00:53:07,717 --> 00:53:09,052
Where is she?

877
00:53:09,052 --> 00:53:09,986
- Gone.

878
00:53:10,554 --> 00:53:12,556
She got away.
- Where?

879
00:53:12,556 --> 00:53:14,391
What did the guy look like?

880
00:53:14,391 --> 00:53:15,725
Where did they go?

881
00:53:15,725 --> 00:53:17,994
- You're the police,
how do I know?

882
00:53:23,800 --> 00:53:26,436
(radio static buzzing)

883
00:53:26,436 --> 00:53:29,439
(suspenseful music)

884
00:53:39,082 --> 00:53:40,217
- Move!

885
00:53:40,817 --> 00:53:41,718
Move!

886
00:53:41,751 --> 00:53:44,020
- I've told you what I know!
- Move, move!

887
00:53:44,054 --> 00:53:45,555
- My bike!
- Move!

888
00:53:45,555 --> 00:53:47,524
(explodes)

889
00:53:47,557 --> 00:53:50,293
(screaming)

890
00:53:55,932 --> 00:54:01,538
(singing in foreign language)

891
00:54:05,442 --> 00:54:06,643
- Police!

892
00:54:07,277 --> 00:54:08,411
Somebody!

893
00:54:09,212 --> 00:54:11,948
Somebody help me, police!

894
00:54:12,249 --> 00:54:13,483
Police!

895
00:54:13,717 --> 00:54:15,619
Please sir, stop.

896
00:54:15,652 --> 00:54:17,687
Telephone, telephone!

897
00:54:25,262 --> 00:54:26,329
(honking)

898
00:54:26,363 --> 00:54:28,498
Hold it, hold it!

899
00:54:31,134 --> 00:54:32,602
Oh, oh!

900
00:54:37,207 --> 00:54:39,876
(phone ringing)

901
00:54:43,480 --> 00:54:44,748
- Hello, oui?

902
00:54:45,282 --> 00:54:46,983
- Inspector Hemery.

903
00:54:46,983 --> 00:54:47,951
Is he there?

904
00:54:48,351 --> 00:54:49,953
- He's off-duty.

905
00:54:49,953 --> 00:54:52,155
- No, no no, he was with me!

906
00:54:52,155 --> 00:54:53,857
- Oh Madame Brennan.

907
00:54:53,857 --> 00:54:55,525
- Has he reported in?

908
00:54:55,925 --> 00:54:57,193
- That he was with you?

909
00:54:57,627 --> 00:54:59,796
- No, about my daughter.

910
00:55:00,363 --> 00:55:03,767
Please, please, I must
speak to the commissaire.

911
00:55:04,968 --> 00:55:06,336
- Well I don't know if--

912
00:55:06,336 --> 00:55:08,838
- For god's sake,
this is an emergency!

913
00:55:08,872 --> 00:55:09,906
- Alright.

914
00:55:12,542 --> 00:55:14,944
- Why hasn't he
reported the kidnapping?

915
00:55:15,345 --> 00:55:17,981
Why aren't the police
looking for my daughter?

916
00:55:19,316 --> 00:55:21,818
- Obviously Inspector Hemery
is still giving chase.

917
00:55:22,052 --> 00:55:24,354
And now you've reported
the kidnapping.

918
00:55:25,088 --> 00:55:27,324
So remain calm.

919
00:55:27,324 --> 00:55:29,993
I'll send a man for you at once.

920
00:55:30,827 --> 00:55:32,662
Where are you?

921
00:55:32,662 --> 00:55:34,064
- I don't know.

922
00:55:34,964 --> 00:55:37,067
They must want the tape.

923
00:55:38,101 --> 00:55:39,469
Where am I?

924
00:55:39,969 --> 00:55:42,539
- You have it then?
- Sir.

925
00:55:42,672 --> 00:55:43,940
Where am I?

926
00:55:45,075 --> 00:55:47,344
- Does Inspector
Hemery have the tape?

927
00:55:47,977 --> 00:55:51,047
- Sir, where am I, where am I?

928
00:55:51,047 --> 00:55:53,016
- Do you see a street sign?

929
00:55:53,016 --> 00:55:54,184
- Here, talk to him.

930
00:55:54,184 --> 00:55:55,518
- Hello, hello?

931
00:55:56,353 --> 00:55:58,221
- This is a police matter.

932
00:55:58,221 --> 00:56:00,523
Give me the location
of the phone booth.

933
00:56:00,523 --> 00:56:03,493
- No monsieur, no monsieur,
I have done nothing.

934
00:56:03,493 --> 00:56:05,362
My immigration papers are good.

935
00:56:05,362 --> 00:56:06,296
- No.

936
00:56:06,629 --> 00:56:08,798
No he doesn't understand you.

937
00:56:09,366 --> 00:56:11,901
Please, okay, thank
you, thank you.

938
00:56:11,901 --> 00:56:15,372
- Just get a taxi and we'll
meet you at the Royal Monsoir.

939
00:56:15,372 --> 00:56:17,574
(dramatic music)

940
00:56:17,574 --> 00:56:20,076
- They knew were we were...

941
00:56:21,878 --> 00:56:22,979
You.

942
00:56:27,784 --> 00:56:30,587
You knew where we were staying.

943
00:56:32,122 --> 00:56:33,189
- Madame Brennan.

944
00:56:34,057 --> 00:56:35,525
- And Hemery too.

945
00:56:36,526 --> 00:56:38,161
- Madame Brennan!

946
00:56:49,806 --> 00:56:50,540
- Taxi.

947
00:56:50,573 --> 00:56:51,174
- Metro?

948
00:56:51,174 --> 00:56:52,709
- Yes, fine, where?

949
00:56:55,211 --> 00:56:57,614
(mysterious music)

950
00:56:57,614 --> 00:57:00,617
(breathing heavily)

951
00:57:23,339 --> 00:57:25,241
- Pretty legs.

952
00:57:30,713 --> 00:57:35,318
If you call out, no
one will hear you.

953
00:57:39,689 --> 00:57:41,591
But if we hear you,

954
00:57:45,929 --> 00:57:47,497
we'll gag you.

955
00:57:48,498 --> 00:57:51,167
So it's up to you.

956
00:58:17,260 --> 00:58:19,929
(phone ringing)

957
00:58:22,465 --> 00:58:23,333
- Oui?

958
00:58:23,333 --> 00:58:24,667
- Bad news.

959
00:58:24,667 --> 00:58:26,636
One of them got away.

960
00:58:28,471 --> 00:58:29,806
- The tape?

961
00:58:30,106 --> 00:58:32,809
- I have the camera
but not the right tape.

962
00:58:32,809 --> 00:58:34,043
- I'll get back to you.

963
00:58:37,580 --> 00:58:39,716
Your friend is an idiot.

964
00:58:39,716 --> 00:58:41,518
- He's not my friend.

965
00:58:41,518 --> 00:58:43,953
I have no use for friends.

966
00:58:43,953 --> 00:58:47,290
- You, you stay with the girl.

967
00:58:48,057 --> 00:58:50,360
We still need her, damn you.

968
00:58:50,360 --> 00:58:51,928
Understand.

969
00:58:53,229 --> 00:58:54,631
Can he be trusted?

970
00:58:58,034 --> 00:58:59,402
- More than him.

971
00:59:26,162 --> 00:59:28,731
(dogs barking)

972
00:59:34,370 --> 00:59:35,538
- You're the one.

973
00:59:36,839 --> 00:59:38,508
You're the one I filmed.

974
00:59:40,076 --> 00:59:42,912
Listen I swear I'm not gonna
say anything to anybody--

975
00:59:42,912 --> 00:59:45,114
- Be quiet.

976
00:59:46,015 --> 00:59:49,118
Who has the tape, Megan?

977
01:00:01,431 --> 01:00:05,335
Would you prefer Briot
to ask the question?

978
01:00:07,003 --> 01:00:10,006
- I don't know who has the tape.

979
01:00:16,980 --> 01:00:19,215
I gave the tape to my
mom and she was gonna

980
01:00:19,215 --> 01:00:23,953
give it to the inspector and
I don't know who has the tape.

981
01:00:33,096 --> 01:00:35,198
- Next time.

982
01:00:57,754 --> 01:00:59,255
- [Daniel] Barbara.

983
01:00:59,255 --> 01:01:00,189
- Stay there.

984
01:01:01,257 --> 01:01:02,792
Where is Megan?

985
01:01:03,593 --> 01:01:05,128
- How did you get in?

986
01:01:05,128 --> 01:01:06,095
- The landlady.

987
01:01:07,397 --> 01:01:08,731
- Why the gun?

988
01:01:08,731 --> 01:01:11,734
- Because one, you and Vandelle

989
01:01:11,768 --> 01:01:13,770
were the only ones who
knew where we were staying.

990
01:01:13,770 --> 01:01:16,039
Two, Luc was sent to our hotel.

991
01:01:16,039 --> 01:01:18,241
Three, whoever wants the
tape will keep Megan alive

992
01:01:18,241 --> 01:01:19,075
until they get it.

993
01:01:19,108 --> 01:01:21,344
Four, you better have
the tape or five,

994
01:01:21,377 --> 01:01:23,980
I will blow your head
off because Megan

995
01:01:23,980 --> 01:01:26,683
is the most important
thing in my life.

996
01:01:26,683 --> 01:01:27,917
That's why.

997
01:01:31,554 --> 01:01:32,622
Uh uh!

998
01:01:35,591 --> 01:01:36,492
Slowly.

999
01:01:40,997 --> 01:01:43,199
- I also suspected my chief.

1000
01:01:45,835 --> 01:01:49,605
If I hadn't, when I
got back to my car...

1001
01:01:50,473 --> 01:01:52,542
You saw me go after Megan.

1002
01:01:52,542 --> 01:01:53,443
- Nice act.

1003
01:01:54,644 --> 01:01:56,079
Quit stalling.

1004
01:01:56,612 --> 01:01:58,281
Where is she?

1005
01:02:00,183 --> 01:02:01,417
- I don't know.

1006
01:02:02,552 --> 01:02:03,619
I don't know why Vandelle

1007
01:02:03,619 --> 01:02:05,688
is involved in
kidnapping, murder--

1008
01:02:05,722 --> 01:02:06,689
- Save it.

1009
01:02:06,823 --> 01:02:07,924
Be quiet!

1010
01:02:09,459 --> 01:02:11,561
- My car was blown up.

1011
01:02:12,562 --> 01:02:14,330
- Go to the phone.

1012
01:02:14,330 --> 01:02:16,232
- They wanted to kill me.

1013
01:02:16,466 --> 01:02:18,468
- Go to the phone!

1014
01:02:19,035 --> 01:02:22,004
- Barbara, this has
gone far enough.

1015
01:02:22,004 --> 01:02:23,239
I am on your side.

1016
01:02:23,239 --> 01:02:26,142
- I want you to call
the American embassy.

1017
01:02:26,142 --> 01:02:27,276
- And?

1018
01:02:27,777 --> 01:02:32,348
- They'll keep the tape
until I get my daughter back.

1019
01:02:32,348 --> 01:02:37,053
- Right now, the fewer people
who know about the tape,

1020
01:02:37,353 --> 01:02:41,124
the more likely it is
that Megan will live.

1021
01:02:42,525 --> 01:02:43,860
- The phone.

1022
01:02:57,140 --> 01:02:59,776
Don't try anything.

1023
01:03:04,881 --> 01:03:06,649
- I thought you knew me.

1024
01:03:09,218 --> 01:03:12,421
When you call your embassy,
they will get in touch

1025
01:03:12,421 --> 01:03:14,090
with my government.

1026
01:03:15,691 --> 01:03:17,160
Is that what you want?

1027
01:03:19,028 --> 01:03:21,731
- I want my daughter.

1028
01:03:22,431 --> 01:03:23,766
(sobbing)

1029
01:03:23,800 --> 01:03:26,369
I want my daughter.

1030
01:03:29,338 --> 01:03:30,673
(guns cocking)

1031
01:03:35,745 --> 01:03:37,680
(knocking)

1032
01:03:42,451 --> 01:03:43,419
- Oui?

1033
01:03:43,419 --> 01:03:48,124
(guns firing)
(screaming)

1034
01:03:50,760 --> 01:03:52,228
Go go!

1035
01:03:54,897 --> 01:03:56,098
Follow me!

1036
01:03:57,366 --> 01:04:00,336
(dramatic music)

1037
01:04:07,743 --> 01:04:09,545
Follow me, quick.

1038
01:04:20,590 --> 01:04:21,858
- Luc.

1039
01:04:25,761 --> 01:04:28,064
- Next door, next door.

1040
01:04:39,041 --> 01:04:41,777
(screaming)

1041
01:04:43,079 --> 01:04:45,781
(guns firing)

1042
01:05:11,007 --> 01:05:12,842
- Your gun!
- Forget it.

1043
01:05:12,875 --> 01:05:14,243
You've got yours.

1044
01:05:14,243 --> 01:05:15,177
- It's a toy!

1045
01:05:15,211 --> 01:05:16,345
- Oh no!

1046
01:05:19,048 --> 01:05:21,550
(guns firing)

1047
01:05:30,359 --> 01:05:31,193
Go!

1048
01:06:14,003 --> 01:06:15,771
- They're coming, go!

1049
01:06:21,143 --> 01:06:23,112
- Don't think about it.

1050
01:06:23,112 --> 01:06:24,947
Just follow me.
- Okay.

1051
01:06:42,798 --> 01:06:45,034
(groaning)

1052
01:06:46,936 --> 01:06:49,538
- Jump, jump, jump!

1053
01:06:52,875 --> 01:06:55,044
(crying out)

1054
01:06:56,979 --> 01:06:58,848
My arm, oh!

1055
01:06:58,881 --> 01:07:01,384
- Oh my god!
- Oh it's broken.

1056
01:07:03,252 --> 01:07:04,186
- Oh!

1057
01:07:07,556 --> 01:07:10,326
(guns firing)

1058
01:07:16,098 --> 01:07:17,733
- The gun, you
know how to use it?

1059
01:07:17,733 --> 01:07:19,602
- No.
- You better learn.

1060
01:07:23,139 --> 01:07:24,807
(gun fires)

1061
01:07:29,745 --> 01:07:32,248
(guns firing)

1062
01:07:37,053 --> 01:07:38,621
Run!

1063
01:07:38,621 --> 01:07:39,588
Run!

1064
01:07:39,622 --> 01:07:40,923
Go, run!

1065
01:07:49,632 --> 01:07:51,400
- They went this way, let's go.

1066
01:07:54,403 --> 01:07:56,272
(suspenseful music)

1067
01:07:56,272 --> 01:07:59,608
(train whistle blowing)

1068
01:08:31,140 --> 01:08:33,642
(guns firing)

1069
01:08:47,923 --> 01:08:50,693
- No!

1070
01:09:05,107 --> 01:09:06,475
Are you okay?

1071
01:09:06,475 --> 01:09:08,010
- Give me the gun!

1072
01:09:08,010 --> 01:09:10,246
(groaning)

1073
01:09:17,653 --> 01:09:20,156
(guns firing)

1074
01:09:28,564 --> 01:09:31,133
(shouts)

1075
01:09:40,643 --> 01:09:42,211
Quick, let's go!

1076
01:09:44,513 --> 01:09:45,681
Go, go!

1077
01:10:12,441 --> 01:10:14,743
(crying out)

1078
01:10:15,711 --> 01:10:17,947
I can't go farther.

1079
01:10:18,214 --> 01:10:19,582
I have to stop.

1080
01:10:20,416 --> 01:10:21,617
- Sit over here.

1081
01:10:27,957 --> 01:10:28,791
Sit.

1082
01:10:34,530 --> 01:10:36,599
- It needs to be set.

1083
01:10:39,868 --> 01:10:42,571
I've got a knife in my pocket.

1084
01:10:50,079 --> 01:10:52,047
(ripping)

1085
01:10:53,482 --> 01:10:55,251
Help me.
- Let me help.

1086
01:10:59,955 --> 01:11:01,257
- Do you know first aid?

1087
01:11:03,692 --> 01:11:05,227
We need splints.

1088
01:11:06,095 --> 01:11:07,463
Do you know splints?

1089
01:11:08,130 --> 01:11:09,198
- Yes.

1090
01:11:10,833 --> 01:11:11,667
Oh.

1091
01:11:30,419 --> 01:11:34,323
- You pull until it
snaps into place.

1092
01:11:35,324 --> 01:11:37,593
And don't let go.

1093
01:11:37,593 --> 01:11:38,594
Okay?

1094
01:11:41,697 --> 01:11:43,232
Harder.

1095
01:11:43,232 --> 01:11:44,867
- I can't.

1096
01:11:44,867 --> 01:11:46,735
- Yes you can.

1097
01:11:46,735 --> 01:11:47,803
Okay.

1098
01:11:47,803 --> 01:11:49,271
Tell me about Megan.

1099
01:11:50,339 --> 01:11:52,741
- She's not what she seems.

1100
01:11:53,575 --> 01:11:56,078
She hides so much.

1101
01:11:57,012 --> 01:12:00,249
I feel like I'm the only
one who can protect her.

1102
01:12:00,282 --> 01:12:02,618
- Love of god, pull!

1103
01:12:02,618 --> 01:12:04,953
- But I'm doing a lousy job.

1104
01:12:05,554 --> 01:12:06,522
- Harder.

1105
01:12:06,655 --> 01:12:09,091
- No I can't!

1106
01:12:10,059 --> 01:12:11,794
(snaps)

1107
01:12:40,989 --> 01:12:42,825
Maybe we should get
you to a hospital.

1108
01:12:42,825 --> 01:12:44,793
- [Daniel] I can't
trust my chief.

1109
01:12:44,793 --> 01:12:47,930
We don't have the luxury
of trusting anyone else.

1110
01:12:47,930 --> 01:12:49,498
Just do it.

1111
01:12:55,471 --> 01:12:56,638
(smashes)

1112
01:12:56,638 --> 01:12:59,274
(alarm blaring)

1113
01:13:06,115 --> 01:13:08,984
- Hey, what do you
think you're doing?

1114
01:13:12,454 --> 01:13:15,290
- We need your keys because
this is an emergency.

1115
01:13:29,738 --> 01:13:32,107
(mysterious music)

1116
01:13:32,107 --> 01:13:35,911
- Hello my pretty
little American.

1117
01:13:35,911 --> 01:13:39,848
It's just you and me here now.

1118
01:13:44,620 --> 01:13:46,121
- Where did you get that?

1119
01:13:46,121 --> 01:13:48,257
- [Briot] Smile for the camera.

1120
01:13:51,193 --> 01:13:53,562
- What did you do to my mom?

1121
01:13:55,764 --> 01:13:57,466
Don't hurt my mom.

1122
01:13:58,033 --> 01:13:59,601
- Smile.

1123
01:13:59,601 --> 01:14:00,636
- Oh god.

1124
01:14:03,639 --> 01:14:05,274
Just let us go home.

1125
01:14:05,274 --> 01:14:09,244
We'll leave France and we'll
never say anything to anybody.

1126
01:14:14,450 --> 01:14:16,351
Did you hurt my mom?

1127
01:14:18,320 --> 01:14:20,389
Oh god, stop it.

1128
01:14:24,726 --> 01:14:26,361
- Maybe I should drive.

1129
01:14:26,728 --> 01:14:28,297
- How?

1130
01:14:28,797 --> 01:14:30,165
- Where are we going?

1131
01:14:30,899 --> 01:14:32,601
- Where does your chief live?

1132
01:14:33,969 --> 01:14:35,704
Which way?
- Fifth exit.

1133
01:14:35,704 --> 01:14:36,939
(honking)

1134
01:14:37,906 --> 01:14:41,443
Oh you're good at this.
- I've had practice.

1135
01:14:45,180 --> 01:14:47,349
(honking)

1136
01:15:01,363 --> 01:15:04,333
- There might be
an alarm system.

1137
01:15:05,567 --> 01:15:06,935
- I'll be careful.

1138
01:15:31,994 --> 01:15:33,061
Psst psst.

1139
01:15:33,929 --> 01:15:34,997
Bark.

1140
01:15:36,765 --> 01:15:39,535
Come on Toto, woof woof.

1141
01:15:40,836 --> 01:15:41,670
Woof!

1142
01:15:42,571 --> 01:15:44,306
(barks)
(cries out)

1143
01:15:44,306 --> 01:15:46,575
(barking)

1144
01:15:59,388 --> 01:16:01,690
- Uh oh Alban.

1145
01:16:02,491 --> 01:16:04,059
In or out?

1146
01:16:04,092 --> 01:16:06,028
Hmm, what's it to be?

1147
01:16:07,195 --> 01:16:10,198
(suspenseful music)

1148
01:17:10,726 --> 01:17:13,395
(clock ticking)

1149
01:17:17,165 --> 01:17:18,834
- What in god's name?

1150
01:17:18,834 --> 01:17:20,268
- Commissaire.

1151
01:17:21,570 --> 01:17:23,271
- How did you get in here?

1152
01:17:23,271 --> 01:17:24,840
- I have something you want.

1153
01:17:25,540 --> 01:17:27,576
And I want my daughter.

1154
01:17:28,310 --> 01:17:31,880
So if you'll just
follow me outside

1155
01:17:32,280 --> 01:17:35,550
we can discuss the exchange.

1156
01:17:36,284 --> 01:17:39,154
- I don't know what
you're talking about.

1157
01:17:39,154 --> 01:17:40,889
- Yes you do.

1158
01:17:40,889 --> 01:17:43,392
Otherwise the tape
is on the news.

1159
01:17:46,695 --> 01:17:47,729
- Okay.

1160
01:17:47,729 --> 01:17:48,964
I need to get dressed.

1161
01:18:20,762 --> 01:18:22,264
The joke's over.

1162
01:18:22,264 --> 01:18:23,598
Where is Hemery?

1163
01:18:23,598 --> 01:18:25,167
(gun cocks)
- Right here.

1164
01:18:26,268 --> 01:18:27,903
You son of a bitch.

1165
01:18:28,537 --> 01:18:29,871
Give it to her.

1166
01:18:34,643 --> 01:18:36,712
- You said you had the cassette.

1167
01:18:43,318 --> 01:18:44,319
- Uh uh.

1168
01:18:45,520 --> 01:18:47,222
Someone has my daughter.

1169
01:18:51,126 --> 01:18:52,961
- I'll see that the
cassette gets delivered

1170
01:18:52,961 --> 01:18:54,362
to the proper person.

1171
01:18:55,263 --> 01:18:57,299
And then your daughter
will be set free.

1172
01:18:57,299 --> 01:18:58,233
- Sure.

1173
01:19:00,168 --> 01:19:01,837
- What choice do you have?

1174
01:19:02,404 --> 01:19:05,507
- We can kill you right now.

1175
01:19:09,211 --> 01:19:11,213
- I know you, Inspector.

1176
01:19:11,747 --> 01:19:13,982
You are too good a policeman

1177
01:19:13,982 --> 01:19:16,051
to shoot a man in the back.

1178
01:19:16,985 --> 01:19:18,687
Especially your commissaire.

1179
01:19:19,054 --> 01:19:20,088
- Yes?

1180
01:19:31,733 --> 01:19:34,669
- And I'm a mother, Barney.

1181
01:19:36,638 --> 01:19:39,407
Does this thing have to
be cocked or something?

1182
01:19:40,475 --> 01:19:42,778
- You pull the trigger.

1183
01:19:57,793 --> 01:20:00,095
- You still lonely
for your mama?

1184
01:20:05,167 --> 01:20:08,737
Or maybe for your
boyfriend back home?

1185
01:20:11,573 --> 01:20:16,978
I bet a cute girl like you
has plenty of boyfriends.

1186
01:20:17,312 --> 01:20:19,181
Dozens of them, maybe.

1187
01:20:19,981 --> 01:20:21,116
Am I right?

1188
01:20:24,519 --> 01:20:28,356
Maybe I could be your boyfriend.

1189
01:20:33,395 --> 01:20:35,130
Soft skin.

1190
01:20:35,897 --> 01:20:40,068
You see, I can be very gentle.

1191
01:20:42,337 --> 01:20:46,374
Most people think
I'm just a tough guy.

1192
01:20:48,877 --> 01:20:52,247
But feel how gentle I am.

1193
01:20:54,549 --> 01:20:57,152
Do you think you could like me?

1194
01:20:57,152 --> 01:20:59,321
- That's enough.
(gasps)

1195
01:21:04,426 --> 01:21:06,394
- What's happened,
where's my mother?

1196
01:21:32,053 --> 01:21:33,255
- [Daniel] What's the layout?

1197
01:21:33,255 --> 01:21:38,460
- Main room, kitchen,
four bedrooms, and
a bath at the rear.

1198
01:21:39,027 --> 01:21:40,095
- Where's Megan?

1199
01:21:43,598 --> 01:21:45,166
Asked you a question.

1200
01:21:45,166 --> 01:21:47,903
- I don't know, I didn't
take care of that.

1201
01:21:49,738 --> 01:21:51,373
- How many are we up against?

1202
01:21:51,373 --> 01:21:52,507
- Three.

1203
01:22:02,817 --> 01:22:03,618
- Move.

1204
01:22:10,659 --> 01:22:13,261
You make a sound, kill you.

1205
01:22:24,105 --> 01:22:24,906
Ready?

1206
01:22:24,906 --> 01:22:26,241
- Yeah.
- Let's go.

1207
01:22:29,778 --> 01:22:32,781
(suspenseful music)

1208
01:23:38,513 --> 01:23:40,548
I don't see Megan.

1209
01:23:46,421 --> 01:23:48,156
We don't know where she is.

1210
01:23:50,025 --> 01:23:52,761
- Just get me into the house.

1211
01:23:52,761 --> 01:23:53,895
- Okay.

1212
01:23:53,928 --> 01:23:54,996
Let's go back.

1213
01:23:59,434 --> 01:24:01,236
- Haven't you
waited long enough?

1214
01:24:04,272 --> 01:24:06,241
No contact, no tape.

1215
01:24:06,241 --> 01:24:09,110
They could have an entire
SWAT team closing in on us.

1216
01:24:10,445 --> 01:24:11,613
- Alright.

1217
01:24:12,080 --> 01:24:14,015
It's time to get out of this.

1218
01:24:16,384 --> 01:24:18,353
Take care of the girl.

1219
01:24:18,353 --> 01:24:21,356
(suspenseful music)

1220
01:24:41,376 --> 01:24:43,645
(groaning)

1221
01:24:54,089 --> 01:24:55,090
- Hungry?

1222
01:25:00,161 --> 01:25:01,229
Thirsty?

1223
01:25:05,366 --> 01:25:07,235
Have to go to the bathroom?

1224
01:25:10,705 --> 01:25:13,007
Light on or off?

1225
01:25:29,958 --> 01:25:31,092
- Where are they?

1226
01:25:31,259 --> 01:25:32,093
- Who?

1227
01:25:32,894 --> 01:25:35,063
- Hemery and the Brennan lady.

1228
01:25:35,096 --> 01:25:36,131
- But where?

1229
01:25:36,131 --> 01:25:37,499
- In the house!

1230
01:25:38,099 --> 01:25:39,300
Get me loose.

1231
01:25:49,511 --> 01:25:53,281
(groaning)
(laughing)

1232
01:26:12,233 --> 01:26:13,334
- Luc.

1233
01:26:15,270 --> 01:26:18,439
Put the gun on the table.

1234
01:26:19,807 --> 01:26:21,976
(gun fires)

1235
01:26:30,385 --> 01:26:31,386
- I'm sorry.

1236
01:26:33,087 --> 01:26:34,556
I'm sorry.

1237
01:26:35,557 --> 01:26:36,357
I'm sorry.

1238
01:26:36,391 --> 01:26:37,759
- Constancia.

1239
01:26:40,662 --> 01:26:41,796
Constancia!

1240
01:26:42,530 --> 01:26:43,998
What are you doing?

1241
01:26:44,032 --> 01:26:45,700
(struggling)
- No!

1242
01:26:45,700 --> 01:26:46,701
No!

1243
01:26:46,701 --> 01:26:47,468
(laughing)

1244
01:26:47,468 --> 01:26:48,536
Stop it!

1245
01:26:48,536 --> 01:26:50,538
Get off of me!

1246
01:26:52,040 --> 01:26:53,374
Get off!

1247
01:26:55,076 --> 01:26:56,377
Stop it!

1248
01:26:59,480 --> 01:27:00,415
Get off!

1249
01:27:00,415 --> 01:27:04,852
(hits)
(shouting)

1250
01:27:08,356 --> 01:27:09,958
- Are you okay?

1251
01:27:13,394 --> 01:27:14,829
- Stop, stop!

1252
01:27:15,997 --> 01:27:18,866
Constancia, Constancia, stop!

1253
01:27:24,272 --> 01:27:25,740
My feet, ah!

1254
01:27:29,944 --> 01:27:32,280
(gun fires)

1255
01:27:33,147 --> 01:27:34,382
Constancia!

1256
01:28:05,113 --> 01:28:06,514
Constancia?

1257
01:28:20,161 --> 01:28:22,864
(crying out)

1258
01:28:32,040 --> 01:28:33,408
Constancia?

1259
01:28:43,484 --> 01:28:47,555
(solemn music)

1260
01:28:51,926 --> 01:28:55,596
- Why, Vandelle, why?

1261
01:29:03,171 --> 01:29:05,073
- I loved her.

1262
01:29:07,141 --> 01:29:09,677
- She was just scenery.

1263
01:29:12,180 --> 01:29:14,248
Two lovers kissing.

1264
01:29:17,719 --> 01:29:21,556
We could have gone home,
nobody would have ever known.

1265
01:29:21,589 --> 01:29:22,957
Nobody.

1266
01:29:40,341 --> 01:29:44,212
(crying)

1267
01:29:49,951 --> 01:29:52,120
(honking)

1268
01:30:24,652 --> 01:30:28,089
Day five, roles reversed.

1269
01:30:28,089 --> 01:30:30,324
Mother in second childhood.

1270
01:30:31,092 --> 01:30:32,427
- Do you mind?

1271
01:30:34,862 --> 01:30:38,766
- Megan, the Arc de
Triomphe is over there.

1272
01:30:38,766 --> 01:30:39,967
- Come on guys.

1273
01:30:40,601 --> 01:30:43,671
- Isn't this what got us into
trouble in the first place?

1274
01:30:45,973 --> 01:30:48,409
- Arc de Triomphe, right.

1275
01:30:56,851 --> 01:31:01,522
(light music)

1276
01:31:05,359 --> 01:31:07,328
Way to go, Mom.

1277
01:31:09,764 --> 01:31:11,399
- Oh.

1278
01:31:11,399 --> 01:31:13,634
(laughing)

1279
01:31:17,872 --> 01:31:19,474
- Hey guys, wait up.

1280
01:31:29,350 --> 01:31:31,853
(light music)

